webnn/ort: assert the sequence in TensorImplOrt::tensor().

tensor_ is GUARDED_BY_CONTEXT(sequence_checker_) but the inline accessor
read it without asserting the sequence, which -Wthread-safety-analysis
rejects (an error in the Windows mono build, the only config that
compiles this backend). The DCHECK states the existing contract — all
callers run on the tensor's sequence — and satisfies the analysis.

--- a/services/webnn/ort/tensor_impl_ort.h	2026-07-08 23:09:50
+++ b/services/webnn/ort/tensor_impl_ort.h	2026-07-08 23:09:50
@@ -36,7 +36,10 @@
   TensorImplOrt(const TensorImplOrt&) = delete;
   TensorImplOrt& operator=(const TensorImplOrt&) = delete;
 
-  OrtValue* tensor() const { return tensor_.get(); }
+  OrtValue* tensor() const {
+    DCHECK_CALLED_ON_VALID_SEQUENCE(sequence_checker_);
+    return tensor_.get();
+  }
 
  private:
   ~TensorImplOrt() override;
